Golfers, Francois Steyn, R Stevens, Tiaan Minnaar and Johan Dreyer were announced the winners of the Polokwane Pro Shop competition played in a four ball alliance, 2 scores to count format at Polokwane Golf Club on Saturday. The team scored 97 points and stayed ahead of their opponents. They were followed by Jacques Lister, Christaan Hoogendyk, MJ Venter and Wynand Scheepers on 90 points. Nola Peceur, Weyden Peceur, Joe Mackays and Charles Mara took the third position on 90 points on a count-out. Daan Kampherbeek, Jan Kampherbeek, Conrad Niewoudt and Cochrane Nel settled for fourth position with 89 points.